org.sbolstandard.core2

Class SequenceOntology

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbolstandard.core2.SequenceOntology

  • public class SequenceOntology
extends Object
    This class provides methods for accessing Sequence Ontology (SO) terms and querying about their relationships.
    Version:
    2.1
    Author:
    Zhen Zhang, Tramy Nguyen, Nicholas Roehner, Chris Myers

        public final String getId(String stanzaName)

        Parameters:
        stanzaName - the name of a stanza
        Returns:
        the matching stanza ID, or null if no match is found.

      • getURIbyName

        public final URI getURIbyName(String stanzaName)
        Returns the URI that is composed of the Sequence Ontology (SO) namespace, i.e. "http://identifiers.org/so/", followed by the ID of an SO term, of the stanza whose name matches the given name. If multiple matches are found, only the first matching one is returned.
        Parameters:
        stanzaName - the name of a term
        Returns:
        the URI of the given SO name

      • isDescendantOf

        public final boolean isDescendantOf(URI childURI,
                                    URI parentURI)
        Returns true if the stanza with childURI is a descendant of the stanza with parentURI. This method first extracts IDs for the child and parent, and then passes them to isDescendantOf(String, String).
        Parameters:
        childURI - the URI of the child stanza
        parentURI - the URI of the parent stanza
        Returns:
        true if the stanza with childURI is a descendant of the stanza with parentURI, or false otherwise
